  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to know about the security of websites in the Status browser.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nDesign update for #4298:\r\n\r\n- For **Status curated DApps and websites with valid `HTTPS` certificate**, show security lock icon in the browser bar. Message on-click:\r\n```Connection is secure. Make sure you really trust this site before signing transactions or entering personal data.```\r\n\r\n[Link to icon SVG ](https://status-im.slack.com/files/U61UDMS5D/FBDG257GA/icon_lock-black.svg)\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/41862274-b9ebee7e-78a3-11e8-9cde-b0354e4ef49b.png\" width =400/>\r\n<br><Br>\r\n\r\n- For **websites with no SSL certificate**, show warning with icon in the browser bar. Message on-click:\r\n```Connection is not secure! Do not sign transactions or send personal data on this site.```\r\n\r\n[Link to icon SVG ](https://status-im.slack.com/files/U61UDMS5D/FBEDL2UNA/icon_lock_opened-black.svg)\r\n\r\n- For **websites with invalid `HTTPS` certificate**, block users from navigating to these sites and present an error page. \r\n\r\n@jeluard which error page do we need here? \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nFor HTTPS sites, a security icon in browser bar displays the appropriate security message on-click.\r\n\r\nFor others, a warning message about the insecure connection is presented. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nA warning message is displayed for any site.",
