    "body": "Sounds good on the first item @jeluard.\r\n\r\nWith regard to HTTP sites, if we don't inject web3, what will be the consequences?\r\n\r\nLet's also add a warning to them. Chrome allows users to visit HTTP sites, but this year they'll be [adding a stronger warning](https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16991254/chrome-not-secure-marked-http-encryption-ssl).\r\n\r\nWith regard to incorrect certificates, should we give users the option to ignore our warning? Sometimes this is possible in browsers like Chrome, under an advanced button, but emphasis is on `Back to safety`.\r\n",
